      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy tests on canonical flows and hemolysis transport equation must demonstrate theoretical convergence rates.",
      "rationale": "Convergence tests were performed on simplified pipe flow but not on rotating impeller geometry relevant to the VAD COU. Order-of-accuracy confirmation for the hemolysis scalar transport equation is absent. Achieved level is below required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation or equivalent on at least three systematically refined meshes covering the full impeller domain; GCI reported for hemolysis QoI.",
      "rationale": "A two-mesh comparison was performed and showed less than 8% difference in bulk flow metrics, but hemolysis index GCI was not computed and the coarsest mesh was not sufficiently refined to establish asymptotic convergence. Achieved level below required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental conditions must replicate all five COU operating points including fluid temperature, hematocrit, and rotational speed with documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Four of five operating points were replicated in bench testing. Hematocrit variation was controlled but temperature was not independently monitored at two test points. Partial coverage yields achieved level below required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative metric (e.g., E_rms) on hemolysis index across all operating points with uncertainty bounds reported.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index predictions were compared to experimental data at four operating points with E_rms of 18%. Uncertainty bounds from Monte Carlo were overlaid but one outlier point was excluded without documented justification. Achieved level below required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The primary QoI (absolute hemolysis index) must be directly measured and compared; surrogate QoIs must be justified.",
      "rationale": "Absolute hemolysis index is used as the primary QoI consistent with COU requirements. Shear stress distributions are reported as supporting QoIs with adequate justification. Minor gap in direct measurement of sub-lethal damage accumulation reduces achieved level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must be conducted on the same pump geometry and at COU-representative operating conditions; any extrapolation must be explicitly bounded.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic pump geometry which approximates but does not replicate the specific VAD impeller geometry. Operating speed range in validation experiments covered only 60% of the COU envelope. Extrapolation beyond validated range is not explicitly bounded. Achieved level substantially below required — this is the primary critical gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence to residual norms below 1e-6 for all transport equations; round-off error assessment documented.",
      "rationale": "Residuals converged to 1e-4 for the hemolysis scalar transport equation; the tighter 1e-6 criterion was met only for momentum equations. Round-off error assessment was not performed. Achieved level below required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented review of boundary condition setup, material property inputs, and post-processing steps by an independent analyst.",
      "rationale": "No independent review of the simulation setup was conducted. Boundary conditions were applied by the same analyst who developed the model without a second-party check. Use error remains a significant unmitigated risk at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis damage model must be justified by comparison to high-fidelity reference data or DNS; sensitivity of hemolysis QoI to model form must be quantified.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on general best practice for rotating machinery; no direct comparison to DNS or LES for this pump geometry was performed. Hemolysis model form uncertainty (power-law vs. strain-based) was not quantified. Model form gap is substantial at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain input parameters must be characterized with probability distributions; Monte Carlo propagation must cover full COU operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo analysis was performed on five input parameters (viscosity, hematocrit, inlet velocity, rotational speed, and hemolysis model coefficients), but geometric manufacturing tolerances and fluid temperature were treated as deterministic. Input uncertainty characterization is incomplete for MRL 5 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Minimum of three independent experimental replicates per operating point with statistical characterization of inter-sample variability.",
      "rationale": "Two replicates were performed at most operating points; only one replicate was available at the highest-speed condition. Inter-sample variability was estimated but not formally characterized with confidence intervals. Sample size is insufficient for MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Computational input parameters must be demonstrated equivalent to experimental conditions through direct measurement or calibrated uncertainty mapping.",
      "rationale": "Inlet flow profiles in simulation were prescribed as uniform; experimental inlet conditions were not measured and assumed to match. Fluid viscosity in experiments was inferred from temperature measurements with significant uncertainty. Equivalency between simulation and experimental inputs is not adequately demonstrated."
    }
